 aturans realm, (2) that it is the will of God + since hat I call Valis is in that realm + not the natura naturata realm (3) the natura naturans realm is sentient, volitional + foresighted (teleology) of the natura naturata realm has total control 526 e i like Spinoza, identify it with natural law (not operating against or despite natural law) but I redefine natural law - well, so does Spinoza. it knows what it is doing, + it knows the exact results of the pressure (valence) it exerts. It is a system of coordinated valences, like a warping web. It works by creating shortest distances. Not somehow it converts time + space back + forth. An increase in space should relax valent pressure + allow greater freedom. Time is space converted into direct pressure. In time, things happen: the natura naturata things are generated. They come about in time as the matrix or receptacle - no; time is pressure that extrudes the naturata, molding them. Then something important regarding this pressure happened to me in 2-74. Time ebbed as in \"Ubik.\" That must mean there was (or I perienced) a massive conversion into space at the expense of time. The organism is elevated out of its falling stone status in which there is only one way it can go + at one specific velocity in which case space has closed around it. (Space has been converted into time, + the object is inder inexorable pressure.) urning space into time: time is the pressure to move through what space is left to it. The law of conservation of motion is involved. (Inertia.) time introduces change. Our consciousness of time's flow is our consciousness of things changing. time tells naturata (things) what to do, so that we do not have a static universe. Time equals God's will, by which everything that is comes into existence 527 when it wishes to exert will, it converts an objects space into time. The result of which is change. This will (pressure) is alive, time it. self is not alive; time is the expression of The will of that which is alive but how much We can learn about God from God's will I don't know, except that his will expressed his intentions; it is God existentially. His will can be read of the changes as process i in the naturata can be read, but this requires memory; here anamnesis is necessary. anamnesis equal's the ability to follow the sequence of changes in terms of pattern (normally we do not remember.) pattern of change to will to God. It's inferential knowledge only, but valid. So - I know what I saw that I call Valis. It is the will of God operating in the naturans realm on the naturata by means of space converted into time as direct pressure to produce change. Every change occurs along the lines of least resistance + the shortest route based on laws of conservation of energy + motion; the divine will determines what is the shortest route + the line of least resistence in terms of pressure or valence. Thus \"warpage away from plumb\" is a change in what is the shortest distance + the line of least resistance nothing can thwart this pressure. The deity is immanent + ubique. There are no miracles, no suspension of natural law, + all is God; but God forms a dialectic of making + breaking So that there is ceaseless change. Process is real. 828 4:20 am the natura naturata realm doesn't exist; hence my acosmism. because of my decades of acosmism t I saw past (beyond bemind, into etc) the naturate realm to the will of God which is the real realm of reality. Thus Valis is real, + the objects which comprise it - of which it is composed - are illusory. As Valis: objects: Ubik: their devolving regressing world. Yes, Valis is a (the) reality support: substantia! So there is a direct connection between my decades of acosmism + my seeing Valis. So in a sense Valis is the objects it imitates, insofar as those objects exist at all. But Valis is not God, but rather the will of There is t God exerted on the naturata. some kind of dialectic perhaps you can only see Valis by disavowing the